cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Researcher: an academic research assistant for Claude Code and Codex"
message: "If you use this software in work that you publish, please cite it."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Sokol
    given-names: Marek
    email: mareksokol98@gmail.com
repository-code: "https://github.com/sokolmarek/researcher"
url: "https://sokolmarek.github.io/researcher"
abstract: >-
  A plugin for Claude Code and Codex covering the academic research pipeline:
  literature search, experiment design, statistical analysis, manuscript
  drafting, visualization, citation management, peer review, revision handling,
  journal and conference selection, and LaTeX or Word publication formatting.
  It is built around integrity constraints: it never fabricates citations and
  never invents data, and it ships mechanical checks (a citation commit guard,
  BibTeX validation against CrossRef with retraction flags, and LaTeX compile
  checks) rather than only asking a model to behave.
keywords:
  - academic writing
  - literature search
  - citation management
  - reproducibility
  - LaTeX
  - large language models
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-07-14"
